verbose_text: Low-dose aspirin therapy did not reduce primary end points in patients with eGFR> = 90 mL/min/1.73 m 2 (aspirin, 9/248; nonaspirin, 11/270; 0.94 [0.38-2.3]) or those with eGFR < 60 mL/min/1.73 m 2 (aspirin, 29/342; nonaspirin, 19/290; 1.3 [0.76-2.4]).
